GH (g=1 permanently):** $y=1$ was detected within 2 cycles.\\n*   **STATE_Y_PERM_LOW (g=0 permanently):** 2 cycles passed without $y=1$.\\n\\n**State Transitions Logic:**\\n1.  **Reset:** If $\\\\text{resetn} == 0$, $\\\\text{state} = \\text{STATE_A}$.\\n2.  **From STATE_A:** If $\\\\text{resetn} == 1$, $\\\\text{state_next} = \\text{STATE_B}$.\\n3.  **From STATE_B (F_Pulse):** $f=1$. $\\\\text{state_next} = \\text{STATE_X1}$ (Start monitoring $x$).\\n4.  **From STATE_X1 (Received $x=1$):** If $x=1$, stay in $\\\\text{STATE_X1}$. If $x=0$, move to $\\\\text{STATE_X0}$.\\n5.  **From STATE_X0 (Received $x=0$):** If $x=1$, move to $\\\\text{STATE_X1_Done}$. If $x=0$, reset sequence, go to $\\\\text{STATE_X1}$.\\n6.  **From STATE_X1_Done (x sequence complete):** $g=1$ on next cycle. $\\\\text{state_next} = \\text{STATE_Y_WAIT_1}$.\\n7.  **From STATE_Y_WAIT_1 (g=1):** If $y=1$, $\\\\text{state_next} = \\text{STATE_Y_PERM_HIGH}$. If $y=0$, $\\\\text{state_next} = \\text{STATE_Y_WAIT_2}$.\\n8.  **From STATE_Y_WAIT_2 (g=1):** If $y=1$, $\\\\text{state_next} = \\text{STATE_Y_PERM_HIGH}$. If $y=0$, $\\\\text{state_next} = \\text{STATE_Y_PERM_LOW}$.\\n9.  **From STATE_Y_PERM_HIGH:** Stay here, $g=1$ permanently.\\n10. **From STATE_Y_PERM_LOW:** Stay here, $g=0$ permanently.\\n\\n**Output Logic (f and g):**\\n*   $f$: $f=1$ only in $\\\\text{STATE_B}$. Otherwise $f=0$.\\n*   $g$: $g=1$ in $\\\\text{STATE_X1_Done}$ (next cycle), $\\\\text{STATE_Y_WAIT_1}$, $\\\\text{STATE_Y_WAIT_2}$, $\\\\text{STATE_Y_PERM_HIGH}$. $g=0$ otherwise (including $\\\\text{STATE_Y_PERM_LOW}$). \\n\\n**Implementation Details & Advice:**\\n1.  **State Encoding:** Use `localparam` for state definitions. Since we need about 8 states, 3 bits are sufficient (2^3=8).\\n2.  **Reset Handling:** The reset is asynchronous/synchronous active-low. The FSM logic handles this by defaulting to STATE_A when $\\\\text{resetn}=0$.\\n3.  **Initialization:** All sequential logic (state register) must be initialized in an 